{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 210°C. Place goose fat in a large ovenproof dish (30 cm x 20 cm x 5 cm) then put in oven to heat.","Place flour, milk, eggs, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then mix <b>12 sec\/speed 6<b>. Set bowl aside, leaving mixture to rest until needed.","Carefully add sausages to hot fat in baking dish and toss to coat, then roast for 15 minutes (210°C) until lightly golden. Turn the sausages then roast for a further 5 minutes (210°C).","Remove hot baking tray from oven and slowly pour in batter; it will sizzle and bubble up a little so be careful. Bake for 30-40 minutes (210°C) until well risen and golden brown, covering with foil halfway through baking time. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 Tbsp goose fat","150 g plain flour","370 g milk","3 large eggs","1 pinch fine sea salt","1 pinch ground black pepper","12 uncooked sausages (approx. 800 g)"]}],"id":"r82709","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-noF9-otrBhE\/XZQwVsLJr1I\/AAAAAAAAclA\/6Nit45seaT0FZqp1OmwSbtmCj8heuecywCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Y7WTF3ap11ECJpFm.png","title":"Toad in the Hole","publishedAt":"2015-12-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"27.4 g","fat":"34.1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"27.9 g","calories":"2206 kJ \/ 527 kcal"},"usefulItems":"rectangular baking dish (approx. 30 cm x 20 cm x 5 cm), aluminium foil, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Hearty and comforting, this inexpensive British classic is quick and easy – making it the perfect midweek supper. You can even make the batter up to 24 hours in advance. Garden peas and onion gravy make perfect accompaniments.","If the batter is made in advance, mix <strong>10 sec\/speed 6<\/strong> before using."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","1h","6 portions"]}